Regression

library("car")                         #
## Loading required package: carData
library("readr")                       #
library("corrplot") 
## corrplot 0.84 loaded
par(family='STKaiti')

hotel <- read.csv("hoteldata.csv")
names(hotel) <- c("hotel_name",        #--
                  "area",              #--
                  "site",              #--
                  "hyg_grade",         #--
                  "ser_grade",         #--
                  "fac_grade",         #--
                  "loc_grade",         #--
                  "evaluate",          #--
                  "time",              #--
                  "type",              #--
                  "price",             #--
                  "lon",               #--
                  "lat",               #--
                  "company",           #--
                  "trip",              #--
                  "school")            #--

hotel$total_grade <- (hotel$hyg_grade+hotel$ser_grade+hotel$fac_grade+hotel$loc_grade)/4
#
hotel$timeCut <- cut(hotel$time, c(0,2015.5,Inf),c("",""))   #
#
hotel$area <- factor(as.character(hotel$area),levels = c("","","",""))

par(mfrow = c(1,1))                                   
hist(x    = hotel$price,
     xlab = "",                          #x
     ylab = "",                                     #y
     ylim = c(0,300),                                  #y
     col  = "lightsteelblue4",                         #lightsteelblue4
     main = "")            

#(2)
median(hotel$price)                                    #
## [1] 1389.5
mean(hotel$price)                                      #
## [1] 1655.513
#1.2
#(1)
par(mfrow = c(1,2))                                    #1x2
hotel$type= factor(hotel$type,levels = c("","",""))
boxplot(log(hotel$price)~(hotel$type),                 #
        col     = "lightsteelblue4",                   #lightsteelblue4
        ylab    = "()",                     #y
        xlab    = "",                            #x
        names   = c("","",""))            #
timeCut <- cut(hotel$time, c(0,2015.5,Inf))
boxplot(log(hotel$price) ~ timeCut,                    #
        col     = c("lightsteelblue4"),                #lightsteelblue4
        ylab    = "()",                     #y
        xlab    = "",                           #x
        names   = c("",""))                  #

#(2)
par(mfrow = c(1,1))                                    #1x1
grade <- data.frame(hotel$hyg_grade,hotel$ser_grade,hotel$fac_grade,hotel$loc_grade)
names(grade) <- c("","","","")
cor_grade <- cor(grade)                                #
corrplot(cor_grade,                                    #
         col         = NULL,
         type        = "full",                         #
         order       = "AOE",                          #(AOE)
         method      = "color",                        #
         tl.col      = "lightsteelblue4",              #lightsteelblue4
         tl.cex      = 1,                              #1
         cl.pos      = "n",                            #()
         addCoef.col = "grey")                         #grey

#(3)
par(mfrow = c(1,2))                                    #1X2
total_gradeCut <- cut(hotel$total_grade, c(0,4.5,Inf)) #
boxplot(log(hotel$price) ~ total_gradeCut,             #
        col     = c("lightsteelblue4"),                #lightsteelblue4
        ylab    = "()",                     #y
        xlab    = "",                            #x
        names   = c("",""))                   #(4.54.5)
evaluateCut <- cut(hotel$evaluate, c(0,median(hotel$evaluate),Inf))
boxplot(log(hotel$price) ~ evaluateCut,                #
        col     = c("lightsteelblue4"),                #lightsteelblue4
        ylab    = "()",                     #y
        xlab    = "",                             #x
        names   = c("",""))               #(4.54.5)

#(1)
lm_price <- lm(log(price) ~ area + type + timeCut + evaluate + total_grade + school + company + trip ,data = hotel)
lm_price <- step(lm_price)                             #AIC
